    <item>
      <title>No Ghosts on Good Street</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/design/noghostsongoodstreet/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/design/noghostsongoodstreet/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Based on a 3D model created by the Fireplace post-production studio, I designed a poster for Emi Buchwald’s award-wining debut. I also prepared the typographic layer for the film.&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex flex-col md:flex-row md:space-x-4&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/niemaduchowwmieszkaniunadobrej/niemaduchowwmieszkaniunadobrej_01.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Poster for Emi Buchwald’s film “No Ghosts on Good Street.” A gray, hairy silhouette is visible from behind against a blue background. The frame includes the creature’s back and head. Above are white letters with information about the film: title, authors.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/niemaduchowwmieszkaniunadobrej/niemaduchowwmieszkaniunadobrej_02.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Polish version of the poster for the Emi Buchwald’s film “No Ghosts on Good Street.” A gray, hairy silhouette is visible from behind against a blue background. The frame includes the creature’s back and head. Above are white letters with information about the film: title, authors.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Clay, Sinter, Form</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/design/claysinterform/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 15 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/design/claysinterform/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The exhibition of ceramics from the collections of the State Ethnographic Museum in Warsaw emphasizes the physicality of the process of creating clay vessels. The objects presented at the exhibition play a key role in a series of posters advertising the event. Using basic visual tools—framing, multiplication, and rythym—I composed micro-scenes and interpreted the stories contained within the objects.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex flex-col md:flex-row md:space-x-4&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/glinaspiekforma/glinaspiekforma_01.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Poster for the exhibition “Clay, Sinter, Form.” Light purple background, brown clay fish in the center. Headline at the top of the composition.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/glinaspiekforma/glinaspiekforma_02.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Poster for the exhibition “Clay, Sinter, Form.” Light brown background, diagonal arrangement of three clay animal figurines in the center. Headline at top of the composition.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/glinaspiekforma/glinaspiekforma_03.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Poster for the exhibition “Clay, Sinter, Form.” Dark purple background, clay vessel at the bottom of the composition. Headline at the top of the composition.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I based the visual identity on a color palette that includes several earthy, clay shades and a complementary purple. Thanks to this, the colors of objects do not clash with the background and you can always choose the right background contrast.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Bleaching</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/design/bleaching/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 29 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/design/bleaching/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The exhibition “Bleaching” concerns the colonial origins of part of the Etnographic Museum’s collection. The visual communication concept is based on two elements: a graphic, symbolic title and a minimalistic typographic frame containing additional information. I created the poster and a graphic design for the exhibition.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex flex-col md:flex-row md:space-x-4&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/wybielanie/wybielanie_01.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;A poster for the “Bleaching” exhibition at a tram stop on a sunny day on a Warsaw street.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/wybielanie/wybielanie_02.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Poster for the “Bleaching” exhibition. Black letters on a white background. The silhouette of the title is blurred, partially erased.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The promotional campaign took place on the streets of Warsaw and online. The typography in the exhibition was printed directly onto the walls using a mobile printer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Phenomenal</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/design/thephenomenal/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/design/thephenomenal/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The exhibition &lt;em&gt;The Phenomenal: Zdzisław Beksiński&lt;/em&gt; took place from April 13 to August 24, 2025, at the National Museum in Wrocław. I developed the visual identity and display design, as well as the design of the catalog accompanying the exhibition.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex flex-col md:flex-row md:space-x-4&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/fenomenalny/fenomenalny_01.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Poster for the exhibition “The Phenomenal: Zdzisław Beksiński” displayed in front of the Four Domes Pavilion in Wrocław.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/fenomenalny/fenomenalny_02.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Poster for the exhibition “The Phenomenal: Zdzisław Beksiński” on a advertising column on a street in Wrocław..&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;one-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/fenomenalny/fenomenalny_03.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Poster for the exhibition “The Phenomenal: Zdzisław Beksiński” on a advertising column on a street in Wrocław.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Zdzisław Beksiński is currently known mainly as a painter, but in the 1950s and 1960s he was involved in photography. Aleksandra Szwedo, the exhibition curator, selected over 150 of his black-and-white photographs, which are characterized by exceptionally precise compositions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>A Slice of the World</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/design/asliceoftheworld/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 15 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/design/asliceoftheworld/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The book, written by historian Błażej Brzostek and published by the Museum of Warsaw, serves as a guidebook that presents a concise history of Poland’s capital through selected objects from the Museum’s collection.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;the-graphic-design-of-the-book-received-the-must-have-quality-mark-during-the-łódź-design-festival&#34;&gt;The graphic design of the book received the Must Have quality mark during the Łódź Design Festival.&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/kawalekswiata/kawalekswiata_01.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Two books stacked on top of each other. On top is the yellow Polish version of “A Slice of the World,” and underneath is the gray English one.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&gt;&#xA;&lt;img&#xA;  src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/kawalekswiata/kawalekswiata_03.webp&#34;&#xA;  alt=&#34;Two versions of the cover for the book “A Slice of the World.” The yellow Polish variant, and the gray English one.&#34;&#xA;  loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;  decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;/&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
